  "chapter": {
    "number": 46,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Babylon’s Idols"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bel crouches; Nebo cowers.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Their idols weigh down beasts and cattle.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The images you carry are burdensome,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a load to the weary animal.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The gods cower; they crouch together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "unable to relieve the burden;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but they themselves go into captivity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Listen to Me, O house of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the remnant of the house of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who have been sustained from the womb,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "carried along since birth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even to your old age, I will be the same,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will bear you up when you turn gray.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have made you, and I will carry you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will sustain you and deliver you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To whom will you liken Me or count Me equal?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To whom will you compare Me, that we should be alike?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They pour out their bags of gold",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and weigh out silver on scales;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they hire a goldsmith to fashion it into a god,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so they can bow down and worship.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They lift it to their shoulder",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and carry it along;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they set it in its place, and there it stands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not budging from that spot.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They cry out to it, but it does not answer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it saves no one from his troubles.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember this and be brave;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "take it to heart, you transgressors!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember what happened long ago,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for I am God, and there is no other;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I am God, and there is none like Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I declare the end from the beginning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and ancient times from what is still to come.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I say, ‘My purpose will stand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all My good pleasure I will accomplish.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I summon a bird of prey from the east,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a man for My purpose from a far-off land.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Truly I have spoken,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and truly I will bring it to pass.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have planned it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will surely do it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to Me, you stubborn people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "far removed from righteousness:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am bringing My righteousness near;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it is not far away, and My salvation will not be delayed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will grant salvation to Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and adorn Israel with My splendor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
